FBIS3-58155 "drweu006aa_94007" FBIS-WEU-94-006 Document Type:Daily Report 10 January 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Leaders Preview NATO Summit; View Expansion, Bosnia Canada's Ouellet Threatens Pullout LD0901214894 Montreal Radio Canada International in English 2130 GMT 9 Jan 94 LD0901214894 Montreal Radio Canada International Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Canada's minister of foreign affairs says that warring factions in Bosnia must realize that the UN peacekeepers' patience there is at an end. He said that if the factions are not interested in making peace, Canada will pull its peacekeepers out of Bosnia and send them home. Mr. Ouellet spoke to reporters in Brussels in advance of tomorrow's NATO summit.
